On Friday, April 04, 2003, at 09:56AM, scott lyons <slyons(-at-)netrover.com> wrote:

>the VDO sender will light the idiot light at anything below 11 psi. the
>stock sender lights the light from 3-6 psi.
>
>put the gauge on and you will see for sure what is going on. i don't know
>about calibrating the VDO sender.

It depends on the model but if you get  VDO 360 006 (M10x1) it's designed to energize the warning contact at 7psi.

The stock sender, 021 919 081B, was 0.15-0.45 bar (2.18-6.53 psi) which is pretty close to the VDO sender.

